title: Grateful Dead Live at Capital Centre on 1979-11-08
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, Stagger Lee, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, It's All Over Now, Don't Ease Me In, Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Morning Dew, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text:
Good find Not clear as to who put this up back in the day. It's said of the Morning Dew of 83 Saratoga as being the best ever, if this had better sound quality I would rank it up there with my favorite Dews.
 All that said thank you for putting this one up maybe it will create more interest and others will post a pristine copy hoping so anyway.

Excellent show....STUPENDOUS Morning Dew....!! Inspired playing throughout the entirety of the show, a real gem from the woefully-underappreciated Fall of 1979.  Everything here is DEFINITELY worth a listen, but the true standout is the MONUMENTAL Morning Dew....it deserves every bit of praise that's been heaped upon it.

Another great Dew that flies under the radar is 4-15-78 Williamsburg.
